                 Philadelphia Prison System

                 For more information about the Prison System, please visit our web
   site.

   Mission

   The mission of the Philadelphia Prison System is to provide a secure
   correctional environment that adequately detains persons accused or
   convicted of illegal acts; to provide programs, services, and
   supervision in a safe, lawful, clean, humane environment; and to
   prepare incarcerated persons for re-entry into society.

   Frequently Asked Questions

   1. How can I find out an inmate's location, Photo ID (PID) number, or
   bail information?
   Call (215) 685-8394, (215) 685-8395, (215) 685-8396, (215) 685-7957, or
   (215) 685-7958. Spanish-speaking persons may call (215) PID number is
   retained throughout an individual's entire criminal career.

   2. When may I visit an inmate?
   Inmates may receive one hour of visits per week. One-half hour must be
   on the inmate's letter-designated visiting day; the other visit may
   take place on any other visiting day. If the inmate's last name begins
   with . . . his or her designated visiting day is:

     * A, B, or C Monday
     * D, E, F, G, or H Tuesday
     * I, J, K, L, or M Wednesday
     * N, O, P, Q, R, or S Thursday
     * T, U, V, W, X, Y, or Z Friday

   Visiting hours are as follows:

   Curran-Fromhold Correctional Facility (CFCF)

   Visits are permitted from 9 a.m. to 10 p.m., Monday through Friday. All
   visitors must sign in by 7:30 p.m. Inmates must obtain unit manager's
   approval for clothing exchanges three days in advance. For more
   information, call (215) 685-7843.

   Detention Center

   Visits are permitted from 9 a.m. to 9 p.m., Monday and Tuesday; all
   visitors must sign in by 7:30 p.m. Visits also are permitted on
   Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday, from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m., and all
   visitors must sign in by 1:30 p.m. Clothing exchanges may be made
   before 1:30 p.m. on the inmate's letter-designated visiting day, when
   inmates obtain captain's approval three days in advance. Call (215)
   685-8447 with any questions.

   House of Correction

   Visits with adult inmates are permitted from 9 a.m. to 9 p.m.,

   Monday through Friday. Visits with juvenile inmates are permitted from
   3 p.m. to 9 p.m., Monday through Friday. Visitors must sign in by 7:30
   p.m. Visitors must present a valid state photo identification card.
   Social service cards are not accepted. Cashier hours are from 9 a.m. to
   12 noon and from 1 p.m. to 2 p.m., Monday through Friday. Clothing
   exchanges must be made before 2:30 p.m. on the inmate's
   letter-designated visiting day. For more information, call (215)
   685-8217.

   Philadelphia Industrial Correctional Center (PICC)

   Visits are permitted from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m., Monday through Friday.
   Visitors must sign in by 5 p.m. Clothing exchanges will be accepted
   only with prior approval by the unit manager. For more information,
   call (215) 685-7100/1.

   ASD-Central Unit, Modular III, Cannery, Ridge Avenue, and University
   Avenue
   Visits are permitted from 9:30 a.m. to 2:30 p.m., Saturday and Sunday.
   Visitors must sign in by 1:30 p.m. Inmates must obtain prior approval
   for clothing exchanges. Approved exchanges will be accepted only during
   visiting hours. For more information, call (215) 685-8730.

   ASD-Youth Study Center Security Unit

   Visits are permitted from 6:30 p.m. to 7 p.m., Monday through Friday.
   Visitors must sign in by 6:30 p.m.

   3. What items may I bring to the inmate I am visiting?
   Approved Items/Limit

     * New bathrobe 1
     * New undershirts (white only) 3
     * New undershorts (any color) 3
     * Thermals (white only) 2
     * New socks 6 pair
     * New pajamas 1 pair
     * New bath towel (maximum size 36" x 18") 2
     * New washcloth (maximum 10" square) 2
     * New panties (female) 7
     * New bra (wireless) 3
     * Prescription eyeglasses, dentures, prosthesis after approval by
       medical department
     * Shoes and sneakers will NOT be accepted.
     * Books, magazines, or periodicals must be sent to the inmate
       DIRECTLY FROM THE PUBLISHER OR COMMERCIAL DISTRIBUTOR.

   4. How can I obtain bail information and where can I pay bail?
   Bail information may be obtained 7 days/24 hours by calling (215)
   685-8394, (215) 685-8395, (215) 685-8396, (215) 685-7957, or (215)
   685-7958. Spanish-speaking persons may call (215) 685-8692.
     * General Sentences
       Criminal Justice Center
       1301 Filbert Street
       Basement Level
       (215) 683-7726/7
       Open 7 days/24 hours
     * Child Support Sentences
       Family Court: 34 South 11 Street, Room B-8
       (215) 686-2926
       Monday  Friday, 9 a.m.  4:45 p.m.
       After hours, bail may be paid at the Criminal Justice Center.
     * Traffic Court Sentences
       Traffic Court: Eighth and Spring Garden Streets
       (215) 686-1565
       Monday  Friday, 8:30 a.m.  6 p.m.
       Saturday, 9 a.m. - 12 noon

   Bail may be paid by cash, money order, certified check, Visa,
   MasterCard, or Discover.

   5. How can I obtain information concerning court dates?
   For Common Pleas Court listings, call (215) 683-7004, (215) 683-7005,
   or (215) 683-7006.
   For Municipal Court listings, call (215) 683-7297.
   Have the inmate's Photo ID (PID) number available.
   For information concerning probation violation hearings, contact the
   Probation Department at (215) 686-6355 or (215) 686-6384, or call the
   defendant's assigned probation officer.

   6. How can I contact an inmate's social worker?
   Curran-Fromhold Correctional Facility (CFCF) - (215) 685-7788
   Detention Center - (215) 685-8452 or (215) 685-8644
   House of Correction - (215) 685-8234 or (215) 685-8232
   Philadelphia Industrial Correctional Center (PICC) - (215) 685-7131
   Alternative & Special Detention - (215) 685-8379

